mode_perl
Tim Tyler's Perl file colouring mode.
For more details there is a help file available.

PERL_FLAGSTOGGLE <word> (ZapPerl Tim Tyler)
This has the same syntax as the WFORMAT_TOGGLE command.  It ticks menu
entries if it is attached to them.

PERL_SETDELAY <byte> (ZapPerl Tim Tyler)
Sets the delay in centiseconds used by bracket matching in the Perl mode.

PERL_SETINDENT <byte> (ZapPerl Tim Tyler)
Sets the size of the indentation in characters used in the Perl mode.

